      <p>Spanish is the official language of the Dominican Republic and a key part of its national identity. The
        Dominican Spanish dialect is distinct, with unique phrases and expressions that reflect the island's history and
        cultural influences. It’s widely spoken across the country and celebrated as a vibrant aspect of Dominican life.
